- updated and tested on CloudStack v3.0.2, for v2.x you may need to adjust id field since new version is using uuid
- support multiple connection profile

(commands):
console\t\trun interactively
cmd-list\tlist available commands
list\t\tlist        [--cmd-opt] (vm|account|site|diskoffering|svcoffering|template|user|job|zone)
deploy\t\tdeploy    [--cmd-opt] (vm)
destroy\t\tdestroy  [--cmd-opt] (vm)
stop\t\tstop        [--cmd-opt] (vm)
start\t\tstart      [--cmd-opt] (vm)
usage\t\tusage -s 2012-05-01 -e 2012-06-01 -a 1 -type (1|2|6)

available cmd-opt on list command:
--param     [comma separated api param]         => 'parameter field'
--response  [comma separated api response]      => 'response field'
--noheader                                      => 'do not print header'
--showparams                                    => 'print supported parameter'
--showresponses                                 => 'print supported responses'
--json                                          => 'print output in json'
--site      [site profile name]                 => 'set site to be use'
--id        [id|uuid]                           => 'set id or uuid for cmd-arg'

Example:
* cloudcmd ls --site branch-profile vm (listing vm using 'branch-profile' connection)
* cloudcmd deploy --soid xxx --tid xxx --zid xxx --name testvm1 --param networkids=xxx  vm
* cloudcmd start --id 1,3,6 vm (start vm with id 1,3 and 6)
* cloudcmd ls --param id=9c2f1c37-e317-45c0-9ec1-82d3216c0678 --response id,displayname,state vm
  (show vm with id 3, only show id,name,state field)
* cloudcmd usage -s 2012-05-01 -e 2012-06-01 -a c6e3d03f-4337-44f2-af04-b4cf28709990 -type (1|2|6)
